The paper proposes a method for dead-reckoning of wheeled vehicles in the context of intelligent vehicles, which suggests that it falls under the robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. The method is based on the use of an Inertial Measurement Unit (IMU) and deep neural networks, which indicates that it may also be relevant to computer vision (cs.CV), machine learning (cs.LG), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of the method for safe emergency stops in the extreme case of exteroceptive sensors failure, which suggests that it may also be relevant to the systems and control (cs.SY) sub-category.
